          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Targets were highly enriched 78Kr gas.",
                "               Batch1          Batch2",
                "     78Kr      99.4%           99.955%",
                "     80Kr       0.6%            0.045%",
                "     82Kr       ---            <0.001%",
                "     83Kr       ---            <0.001%",
                "chemical purity  99%           99.04%",
                "supplier     Isotec, USA     Chemotrade, Germany"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "EXTB",
                "STTA",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "- Stacked gas target technique was used.",
                "- Cylindrical stainless steel cells 20mm in diam. 25",
                "  mm length.",
                "- 15 micron thick kapton (polyimid) and 25 and 50",
                "  micron thick Al windows were used.",
                "- Gas pressure 0.42-0.92 bar.",
                "- Ti (12.5 and 20 microns) and Cu (10 micron) foils",
                "  were used as monitor foils.",
                "- Beam intensity was 100-200 nA and was measured in",
                "  Faraday cup.",
                "- Maximum difference between the values measured by",
                "  Faraday cup and deduced from monitor reactions was",
                "  20%.",
                "- Primary energies were between 7.4 and 14.3 MeV.",
                "- Nine irradiations were done.",
                "- High resolution gamma spectrometry was applied",
                "  without chemical separation. Spectra were measured",
                "  after the total decay of the short lived isomer",
                "  states.",
                "- The stacks contained 3-5 cells.",
                "- Energy degradation was calculated by using the",
                "  polynomial approximation of Andersen and Ziegler.",
                "- Energy scale and beam intensity along the stacks",
                "  were corrected according to the applied monitor",
                "  reactions.",
                "Decay data were taken from R.B. Firestone",
                "Table of Isotopes."
              ]
            }
          ],
